{
  "stem": "13817.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Everybody had to give 25% of his wealth to the Nazis, because these-- the Jews were at fault for the Kristallnacht.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now a funny thing is-- I don't know whether you realize that-- the 9th of November has a lot of meaning for German things.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "First of all, in 1923, I think this was actually the reason the 9th of November was chosen for the-- for the Kristallnacht.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In 1923, Hitler had the first run-in with the police.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The Nazi Party had the first run-in with the police in Munich, in Munchen, about the-- the tried-- so-called putsch there.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They wanted to overthrow the city, the government.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they had a clash with the police where-- I don't remember how many-- Nazis were killed at that time.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He had a song there, we'll never forget you, your deaths from the 9th of November.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The Nazis had that song.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But also the Weimar Republic went down on the 9th of November.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The 9th of November was a other deal.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He, he started his so-called SS, special troops, on the 9th of November.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And other things happened all the time in the German history what comes out to the 9th of November.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "In fact, the Berlin Wall came down on the 9th of November.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I don't know why this always repeats itself, but this seems a date what, what has a significant meaning to Germany.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Well, after that, then everybody had to give up their jewelry or their, their fur coats.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Their stock had to be registered and was taken away.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "The businesses where closed by the-- with the 31st of December in '38.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Jews couldn't have any more businesses.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the business had to be closed from November-- from 9th of November till-- till December 31, or '38.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
